  <notes notes-type="data-availability">
    <title>Code availability</title>
    <p>TYGS is a web service that fulfills end-user requirement of the journal for web tools by providing the service free and publicly accessible with any modern web browser. The underlying TYGS database is implemented in the object-relational database system PostgreSQL (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://www.postgresql.org/">https://www.postgresql.org/</ext-link>). The TYGS workflow engine is written in the programming language Ruby (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/">https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/</ext-link>), whereas the TYGS web server is implemented in Rails 5, a modern web application development framework (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://rubyonrails.org/">https://rubyonrails.org/</ext-link>). The web application makes use of Bootstrap 3.3.7, a free and open-source front-end framework (library) for designing websites and web applications (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://getbootstrap.com/">https://getbootstrap.com/</ext-link>), and PhyD3<sup><xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR68">68</xref></sup> for the visualization of phylogenetic trees.</p>
